{"id":44526,"title":"Adenocarcinoma arising in a tailgut cyst: a case report.","abstract":"Tailgut cyst (TGC), also called retrorectal hamartoma, is a rare congenital lesion arising from persistent remnants of the postanal gut. Malignant transformation of TGC is exceedingly uncommon. We report herein the clinicopathologic features and the follow-up of a new case of a TGC with adenocarcinomatous transformation occurring in a 61 year-old woman.","date":"2014-04-15","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24730339","annotations":[{"name":"Malignant transformation","weight":0.697993,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malignant_transformation"},{"name":"Transformation (genetics)","weight":0.573737,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transformation_(genetics)"},{"name":"Cyst","weight":0.154985,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyst"},{"name":"Adenocarcinoma","weight":0.138889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adenocarcinoma"},{"name":"Malignancy","weight":0.130838,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malignancy"},{"name":"Hamartoma","weight":0.129468,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamartoma"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.0549849,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.0210801,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Human gastrointestinal tract","weight":0.0209876,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_gastrointestinal_tract"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Case report","weight":0.0148276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Case_report"},{"name":"Tailpiece","weight":0.013127,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tailpiece"}]}
